sect3.para:
So in addition, you should select exactly one C/C++ source file that actually instantiates the code, preferably a file you're not editing frequently. This file should define a specific macro (this is documented per-library) to actually enable the function definitions. For example, to use stb_image, you should have exactly one C/C++ file that doesn't include stb_image.h regularly, but instead does #define STB_IMAGE_IMPLEMENTATION
#include "stb_image.h"
 The right macro to define is pointed out right at the top of each of these libraries.
